Module org.microbean.invoke

Package org.microbean.invoke

package org.microbean.invoke
Provides classes and interfaces related to concepts embodied by the java.util.function and java.lang.invoke packages.
Author:
Laird Nelson
See Also:
  • BootstrapMethods
  • ConstantBootstraps
  • Class
    Description
    BootstrapMethods
    Useful constant bootstrap methods and methods that make sense to invoke from ConstantBootstraps.invoke(Lookup, String, Class, MethodHandle, Object...).
    CachingSupplier<T>
    A DeterministicSupplier that computes the value it will return from its CachingSupplier.get() method when that method is first invoked, and that returns that computed value for all subsequent invocations of that method.
    ConstantDescs
    A utility class containing various ClassDesc constants.
    DeterministicSupplier<T>
    A Supplier that may be deterministic.
    OptionalSupplier<T>
    A DeterministicSupplier with additional contractual requirements.
    OptionalSupplier.Absent<T>
    An OptionalSupplier implementation that indicates permanent absence.
    OptionalSupplier.Presence
    A token indicating transitory or permanent presence or absence.
    OptionalSupplier.Present<T>
    An OptionalSupplier implementation that supplies a fixed value.
